[
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"519727\">@Alice Ryhl</span> does every payload <code>foo</code> one enqueues with <code>workqueue::system().enqueue(foo)</code> have to implement <code>Send</code> and <code>Sync</code>? Can't you pass <code>foo</code> by value?</p>",
        "id": 583199192,
        "sender_full_name": "Philipp Stanner",
        "timestamp": 1775115337
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The implementation:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">enqueue</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ID</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u64</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">W</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">W</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">EnqueueOutput</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">RawWorkItem</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">ID</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Send</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>requires <code>Send</code>, but accepting \"by value\" sounds good too I think.</p>",
        "id": 583219748,
        "sender_full_name": "Onur Özkan",
        "timestamp": 1775121814
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So the answer is: you can't pass <code>foo</code> by value (if it doesn't implement <code>Send</code>) at the moment.</p>",
        "id": 583220017,
        "sender_full_name": "Onur Özkan",
        "timestamp": 1775121885
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>OK, thx.<br>\nIt indeed sounds reasonable to me to have that for \"fire and forget\" work</p>",
        "id": 583220321,
        "sender_full_name": "Philipp Stanner",
        "timestamp": 1775121970
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The workqueue is a separate thread, and <code>Send</code> is required to touch a value from a separate thread, so yes it's required. I'm not sure what you mean by \"Can't you pass <code>foo</code> by value?\" because <code>Send</code> is required <em>and</em> you pass by value.</p>",
        "id": 583222145,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1775122472
    }
]